{
  "stem": "23090.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was-- I had a tutor, a rabbi tutor, who-- who was teaching me Hebrew, which was almost a criteria when you were a young Jewish child-- boy-- in that era.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was required, by the Polish government, to go to-- attend the normal school, which I believe was about to the second grade.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "My learning in that capacity was limited, since it was just beginning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, of course, the interruption, so it all went for naught just when the ghetto-- when I was placed in a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But that was the extent of my schooling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, the only Jewish-- the only Jewish schooling that we would get would be from the Hebrew end, or from the cheder end.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But the-- the Polish system had a fairly adequate public school system, which [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] was, I imagine, impressive looking back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were required to attend the-- those public schools.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So yes, I did go to school to the point that-- 'til the point of the war-- the time of the war.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was a problem, because that, too, was something you were growing up with.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And it was a-- it was a difficult task to be a Jewish child in a public school in Poland in those days, because we were always [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] harassed and called dirty Jews, and so on, and so forth, which, of course, was stemmed out of a-- a-- generations of that kind of a mentality.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were sort of persecuted, in a different way, by the-- by the Polish-- by the Polish people.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I'm not saying all of them, but we heard it on a normal, regular basis-- [NON-ENGLISH], which meaning is Jew.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
